cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses privacy infringement and countermeasures related to online tracking and profiling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also discusses the importance of privacy literacy and user autonomy in the information society, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The analysis of interest profiling by Google involves data mining and machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the user experience and interaction with online tracking profiles, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves analyzing links lists and developing countermeasures, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
